This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with object detection. It also involves deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel framework for few-shot detection, which involves adapting to new environments, indicating that it could be categorized under robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of relational clues, which suggests that it could be categorized under neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
